---
Manage chat sessions through their full lifecycle.

Lifecycle: create -> configure -> send -> pause -> resume -> end

Examples:
  cru session create --title "My task"           # Create and name a session
  cru session configure <id> -p openai -m gpt-4  # Set backend
  cru session send <id> "message"                 # Send and stream response
  cru session pause <id>                          # Pause
  cru session resume <id>                         # Resume from paused
  cru session end <id>                            # End when done

  cru session list                                # List recent sessions
  cru session show <id>                           # Show session details
  cru session open <id>                           # Open in TUI
  cru session export <id> -o session.md           # Export to markdown
  cru session search "rust"                       # Search by title

Scripting (non-interactive):
  ID=$(cru session create -q)                     # Capture session ID
  CRU_SESSION=$ID cru session send "hello"        # Use env var

Usage: session <COMMAND>

Commands:
  list       List recent sessions
  search     Search sessions by title
  show       Show session details
  open       Open a previous session in the TUI (same as `cru chat --resume`)
  export     Export session to markdown file
  reindex    Rebuild session index from JSONL files
  cleanup    Clean up old sessions
  create     Create a new daemon session
  pause      Pause a daemon session
  resume     Resume a paused daemon session
  end        End a daemon session
  send       Send a message to a session and stream response
  configure  Configure agent backend (provider + model + endpoint) for a session. Use `cru set` for runtime parameter tweaks (temperature, thinking_budget, etc.)
  load       Load a persisted session from storage into daemon memory
  help       Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
